{{Orphan|date=February 2015}} {{Infobox power station | name = Jiayuguan Solar Park | name_official = | image = | image_size = | image_caption = | image_alt = | location_map = China | location_map_size = | location_map_caption = | coordinates = {{coord|39|41|N|99|00|E|region:CN_type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | country = [[China]] | location = [[Jiayuguan City]] | status = O | construction_began = | commissioned = | decommissioned = | cost = | owner = | operator = | solar_type = pv | solar_site_area = | ps_electrical_capacity = 52 [[Megawatt|MW]] | ps_electrical_cap_fac = | website = | extra = }} The '''Jiayuguan Solar Park''' is a 52 MWp [[photovoltaic power station]] located in the [[Jiayuguan City]] region, in [[China]]. It uses fixed tilt arrays.<ref>[http://www.pv-tech.org/news/clenergy_adds_12mw_to_40mw_pv_project_in_jiayuguan Clenergy adds 12MW to 40MW PV project in Jiayuguan]</ref><ref>[http://news.pv-insider.com/photovoltaics/pv-intelligence-brief-22-june-%E2%80%93-3-july-2012 PV Intelligence Brief 22 June – 3 July 2012]</ref><ref>[http://solarprofessional.com/resources/press/details/?PressID=814 Clenergy's Jiayuguan 40MW project contract increased to 52MW]</ref> The first stage, 40 MWp, was completed in 2012.
