{{short description|A hypothetical form of dark matter consisting of particles with strong self-interactions}} In [[astrophysics]] and [[particle physics]], '''self-interacting dark matter''' ('''SIDM''') assumes [[dark matter]] has self-interactions, in contrast to the collisionless dark matter assumed by the [[Lambda-CDM model]]. SIDM was postulated in 2000 to resolve a number of conflicts between observations and [[N-body simulations]] (of cold collisionless dark matter only) on the galactic scale and smaller.<ref name="sper">{{Cite journal |first1=David N. |last1=Spergel |authorlink1=David Spergel |first2=Paul J. |last2=Steinhardt |authorlink2=Paul Steinhardt |title=Observational evidence for self-interacting cold dark matter |journal=Physical Review Letters |volume=84 |issue=17 |pages=3760–3763 |date=24 April 2000 |arxiv=astro-ph/9909386 |doi=10.1103/PhysRevLett.84.3760|bibcode = 2000PhRvL..84.3760S |pmid=11019199}}</ref><ref name="wand">{{cite conference |first1=Benjamin D. |last1=Wandelt |first2=Romeel |last2=Davé |first3=Glennys R. |last3=Farrar |first4=Patrick C. |last4=McGuire |first5=David N. |last5=Spergel |authorlink5=David Spergel |first6=Paul J. |last6=Steinhardt |authorlink6=Paul Steinhardt |title=Self-Interacting Dark Matter |location=Marina del Rey |year=2000 |conference=Dark Matter |arxiv=astro-ph/0006344 |url=http://physics.princeton.edu/~steinh/IntDarkMatter3.pdf|bibcode=2001sddm.symp..263W }}</ref> It was also used to explain the 2015 observations of [[ESO 146-5]] the core of the [[Abell 3827]] galaxy cluster.<ref name=Massey2015/> However, the latter finding has since been discounted based on further observations and modelling of the cluster.<ref>{{cite arxiv| title=Dark matter dynamics in Abell 3827: new data consistent with standard Cold Dark Matter | display-authors=etal | last1=Massey | first1=Richard |eprint=1708.04245 | date=August 2017 |mode=cs2| class=astro-ph.CO }}</ref><ref>{{citation | title=Dark matter isn’t interacting with itself after all | work=ScienceNews | publisher=Society for Science & the Public | first1=Lisa | last1=Grossman | date=April 5, 2018 | url=https://www.sciencenews.org/article/dark-matter-isnt-interacting-itself-after-all | accessdate=2018-04-05 | postscript=. }}</ref>
Self-interacting dark matter has also been postulated as an explanation for the [[DAMA/NaI|DAMA]] annual modulation signal.<ref name="mit">{{Cite journal |first=Saibal |last=Mitra |title=Has DAMA detected self-interacting dark matter? |journal=Physical Review D |volume=71 |issue=12 |page=121302 |date=15 June 2005 |arxiv=astro-ph/0409121 |doi=10.1103/PhysRevD.71.121302|bibcode = 2005PhRvD..71l1302M }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.scientificamerican.com/article/dark-matter-may-feel-a-dark-force-that-the-rest-of-the-universe-does-not1 |publisher=[[Scientific American]] |title=Dark Matter May Feel a "Dark Force" That the Rest of the Universe Does Not |first1=Clara |last1=Moskowitz |date=20 April 2015}}</ref><ref name=Massey2015>{{cite journal |url=http://mnras.oxfordjournals.org/content/449/4/3393 |journal=Monthly Notices of the Royal Astronomical Society |volume=449 |issue=4P |pages=3393–3406 |date=June 2015 |title=The behaviour of dark matter associated with four bright cluster galaxies in the 10 kpc core of Abell 3827 |doi=10.1093/mnras/stv467|arxiv = 1504.03388 |bibcode = 2015MNRAS.449.3393M |author=Richard Massey et al.}} commentary [https://scitechdaily.com/the-possible-first-signs-of-self-interacting-dark-matter/ The Possible First Signs of Self-interacting Dark Matter]</ref>
==See also== *[[MACS J0025.4-1222]], astronomical observations that constrain DM self-interaction *[[ESO 146-5]], the core of [[Abell 3827]] that was claimed as the first evidence of SIDM *[[Strongly interacting massive particle]] (SIMP), proposed to explain cosmic ray data
