The '''Yuzivska gas field''' is a [[Ukraine|Ukrainian]] [[natural gas field]] that was discovered in 2010. It will begin production in 2017 and will produce [[natural gas]] and [[Natural gas condensate|condensates]]. The total [[proven reserves]] of the Yuzivska gas field are around 70.8 trillion cubic feet (2000×10<sup>9</sup>m³) and production is slated to be around 960 million cubic feet/day (27.4×10<sup>6</sup>m³). The total exploration investment is expected to range between 250-300 million US$. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2012/05/16/ukraine-gas-shale-idUSL5E8GGAJY20120516|title=Ukraine sees 2017 for commercial shale gas output|date=2012|publisher=Reuters|accessdate=2014-08-11}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rferl.org/content/ukraine-fracking-shale-gas-russia/24881720.html|title=Kyiv Turns To 'Unconventional' Natural Gas To Wean Itself From Gazprom|date=2013|publisher=rferl.org|accessdate=2013-05-31}}</ref>
